    <div class="sg-demo-block prose" style="max-width:560px">
      <h2>Design systems that scale</h2>
      <p>A design system isn't a component library. That's the mistake I see most teams make. A component library is a collection of UI elements. A design system is the <strong>shared language</strong> — the decisions, principles, and documentation.</p>
      <blockquote>The best design system is the one your team actually uses.</blockquote>
      <h3>What gets teams in trouble</h3>
      <p>Nobody could answer <a href="#">"is this in the design system?"</a> with confidence. You can use <code>var(--accent)</code> inline like this.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Document the why, not just the what</li>
        <li>Treat inconsistency as a bug</li>
        <li>Design systems are living docs</li>
